docs.abstract: The Japanese conglomerate wants to build a top private equity firm, its latest move to shake up an entrenched industry. Wall Street is skeptical.

headline.main: SoftBank Looks to Invade Wall Street’s Turf
headline.print_headline: SoftBank Moves to Muscle Into Private Equity

docs.abstract: Facebook said it planned to prioritize high-quality news on its site by allowing its users to rank news sources that they see as the most credible and trustworthy.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook said on Friday that it planned to prioritize high-quality news on the social network by allowing its users to rank news sources that they see as the most credible and trustworthy.

headline.main: Facebook to Let Users Rank Credibility of News
headline.print_headline: Facebook Will Let Users Rank Credibility of News

docs.abstract: Most executives who have testified before Congress will tell you that there is no such thing as “winning.” But Facebook’s C.E.O. could walk away with a small but critical victory.
docs.snippet: Most executives who have testified before Congress will tell you that there is no such thing as “winning.” But Facebook’s C.E.O. could walk away with a small but critical victory.
docs.lead_paragraph: Most crisis-embattled executives who have been compelled to testify before congressional committees will tell you that there is no such thing as “winning.” The only truly possible outcomes, they will say, are losing or losing disastrously.

headline.main: How Mark Zuckerberg Can ‘Win’ on Capitol Hill

docs.abstract: The New York Times would like to hear from servers and diners about their experiences with tipping.

docs.lead_paragraph: Amid a cultural reckoning over misconduct in the workplace, we spoke to more than 60 restaurant servers and bartenders, who shared stories of having to endure crude comments and even groping from customers — all to ensure a good tip.

headline.main: What Is Your Experience With Tipping in Restaurants?
